cyclone.name: LAURA
cyclone.current_location: about 15 mi (25 km) south of Cayo Largo, Cuba
cyclone.trajectory: moving WNW, forecast to cross western Cuba this evening and then track northwestward across the central and north-western Gulf of Mexico toward the Texas–Louisiana coast
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: north-western Gulf Coast near the Texas–Louisiana border

weather_observation.watch_coast: Tropical-storm watch/warning presently limited to portions of Cuba, Little Cayman/Brac, Florida Keys; none issued for the U.S. Virgin Islands
weather_observation.warning_coast: Tropical-Storm Warning in effect for Little Cayman, Cayman Brac, many Cuban provinces, and the Florida Keys from Craig Key to Key West including the Dry Tortugas
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Southern and western Cuba, Cayman Islands, Florida Keys, and forecast later for the north-western Gulf Coast
